      },
      {
        "step_no": 2,
        "text": "Prepare dressing: combine lime juice, fish sauce, palm sugar, minced garlic and sliced chilies in a small bowl and stir until sugar dissolves; taste and adjust balance of sour/salty/sweet.",
        "time_min": 4
      },
      {
        "step_no": 3,
        "text": "Season steak lightly with salt and pepper and brush with oil; preheat a grill or heavy skillet over high heat until very hot.",
        "time_min": 3
      },
      {
        "step_no": 4,
        "text": "Sear the steak on the hot grill or pan until well browned and medium-rare to medium (about 3-4 minutes per side depending on thickness); use a thermometer if desired and remove when internal temperature reaches 130-135Â°F for medium-rare.",
        "time_min": 8
      },
      {
        "step_no": 5,
        "text": "Rest the steak for 5 minutes on a cutting board to allow juices to redistribute, then slice thinly across the grain into bite-sized pieces.",
        "time_min": 6
      },
      {
        "step_no": 6,
        "text": "In a large bowl, toss sliced steak with the dressing, ground toasted rice, thinly sliced shallot, green onions, fresh herbs, cucumber and lettuce if using; toss gently to combine and coat evenly.",
